      "@type": "hosc:ConformanceAssertion",
      "name": "There is ONE canonical holospace shell (os/usr/share/frame/shell.html, in OS2) — the default AND only launcher for every app in the Hologram Apps catalog. Every shell decider routes to it (the rEFInd boot loader · the SDDM interposition · the greeter's default session + fallback · holospace.html's normal-link projection · the dev server's '/'), the duplicate shells are retired (no second default boot, no duplicate shell code — apps/browser and apps/sdk removed, live + vendored), and the rule is ENFORCED for every app: any app that ships its own top-level tab strip must carry the ONE shared embed guard (holo-embed.js + html[data-embedded]) so it drops that chrome when hosted in the shell — no app double-draws the frame. The runtime suppression itself is proven by booting Holo Files embedded in real Chromium (holo-files row).",
      "hosc:authority": "holospaces Laws L1 (content not location) · L2 (canonical forms only) · L4 (everything through the substrate) · L5 (verify by re-derivation) — docs/08-Concepts §Canonical forms and κ-labels · UOR-ADDR (κ-label = <axis>:<hex> = H(canonical_form)) · the substrate σ-axis BLAKE3, KAT-proven byte-identical to hologram's kappa() (the EXTERNAL κ-addressing oracle, witnessed by tools/holo-blake3-witness.mjs — not self-reference) · W3C DID Core (the did:holo:blake3 alsoKnownAs alias) · W3C Subresource Integrity + multibase · W3C iframe sandbox + Permissions-Policy (the app canvas) · real Chromium via the holo-files row (embed suppression)",
