      "@type": "hosc:ConformanceAssertion",
      "name": "Every holospace exposes a SINGLE UNIFIED REST API at /~<app>/api — a standardized, content-addressed κ-stream surface for the open semantic web (humans · external API-gated apps · agents), over the SAME κ-store/registry as MCP (no parallel infrastructure, Law L4). INGRESS (POST /o, POST /stream) imports objects → their κ (the server re-derives the address, Law L2); EGRESS (GET /o/<κ>, GET /stream as NDJSON/SSE) exports SELF-VERIFYING UOR objects (re-derive to verify, Law L5). The descriptor is OpenAPI 3.1 ⊕ JSON-LD (the REST twin of the MCP capability card). Monetisation is HTTP 402 pay-per-κ-object-stream with a REAL token rail: the payer SIGNS a κ-bound permit (binding app + resource κ + amount + nonce + deadline) verified LOCALLY by ed25519 (no node, no chain — verify-by-re-derivation applied to money, no trusted-amount field), and the permit is CONSUMED single-use in a content-addressed spend ledger (a self-verifying holo:Spend chain → replay refused as already_spent); the permit is presented directly for pay-per-κ or POSTed to /settle for a time-boxed self-verifying entitlement. It is WIRED TO HOLO WALLET + the PLASMA stablecoin rail: a 402 names the exact gas-abstracted USD₮0 (or any token) transfer, and fetchPaid() drives the wallet's default-deny human-approval seam to pay it and retries — one tap unlocks the stream; the Plasma tx is single-use (replay refused), bound to the app's payout address + the resource κ, with on-chain finality as a pluggable confirm adapter; fiat is also a pluggable adapter. The engine is node-free (isomorphic) and mounted on every tier — the dev server AND the serverless Service Worker (no origin server)",
      "hosc:authority": "OpenAPI 3.1 · schema.org + W3C JSON-LD 1.1 + PROV-O · HTTP 402 Payment Required (x402/L402 family) · W3C Service Workers · UOR content-addressing (Law L1/L2/L4/L5)",
