      "name": "ROUTING PLANE — typed semantic streams (Holo Route, ADR-0069): the THIRD composition boundary, the *data* boundary, beside Holo Link's *call* boundary (ADR-0060) and Holo Orchestrate's *collaboration* boundary (ADR-0045). A pipeline is a content-addressed dataflow graph of deterministic κ-transforms — `pipe(a).to(b).to(c)` — whose SEAMS are type-checked by re-derivation BEFORE a byte flows (a type-mismatched seam, or a stage missing its entry export, is refused at assembly with a precise message); the HOST is the pipe — it lowers a typed value (i32 · str · bytes) into a stage's OWN linear memory and lifts the result back, the canonical-ABI lift/lower at the stage boundary (Holo Link's isolated-component model); each stage runs as a verifiable κ-transform accepted only after re-deriving its κ (Law L5); a shared (stageκ ⊕ inputκ) is an O(1) rebind (Law L3); the conscience gates each stage dispatch (ADR-0033, fail-closed); and the whole run SEALS as one self-verifying PROV-O κ any peer re-runs with no server — a tampered stage OR a tampered seal refuses the whole pipeline. Being an object, the pipeline is shareable · ownable · settleable · delegable. The UNIX pipe, typed and verifiable; mint nothing",
