      "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-control",
      "@type": "hosc:ConformanceAssertion",
      "name": "OBSERVABILITY COMMAND CENTER — Holo Control (the telemetry monitoring & control dashboard, ADR-0073 consumer): models the whole system as a graph (this OS at center, every external interaction a governable edge — app · agent · resource · human · wallet) and stays CALM BY DEFAULT via a robust signal-processing core. This row witnesses that core (tools/holo-control-dsp-witness.mjs, pure + deterministic): a noise floor from median + MAD (a few loud spikes do NOT inflate it and hide the next signal); a robust z-score (a degenerate window does not divide by zero); an EMA low-pass (steady-state) + first-difference high-pass (change); SALIENCE = magnitude × novelty × governance-risk (egress / wallet-out / agent-write weigh heaviest), so ranking surfaces the one thing worth the operator's eyes; thresholding WITH hysteresis (an alert latches at the high gate, releases below the low gate — it cannot flap); an aggregate SNR (the fraction of activity that is genuine signal); and a matched filter for the exfiltration signature (sustained egress to a NEW destination), distinct from a lone spike. The app is additionally render-witnessed in a real browser (tools/holo-control-render-witness.mjs, committed result): it boots, binds the Holo UI tokens, populates REAL edges from the live catalog, ranks/switches/inspects, runs a conscience-gated control action that seals a verifiable receipt, and is HONEST where a feed is unwired (no fabricated flows/balances/presence). Local-first; the dashboard observes and nothing leaves the device unasked",
      "hosc:authority": "robust statistics (median / MAD, 1.4826·MAD ≈ σ) · classical DSP (EMA low-pass, first-difference high-pass, SNR dB, matched filter) · Holo Telemetry (ADR-0073) signals · the Holo Constitution (ADR-0033, the control conscience gate) · holospaces Laws L1 (private-first, local) / L5 (deterministic re-derivation)",
      "hosc:witness": "tools/holo-control-dsp-witness.mjs",
      "hosc:required": true,
      "hosc:category": "Compute & verifiable builds"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://hologram.os/conformance/os2#holo-compose-mcp",
      "@type": "hosc:ConformanceAssertion",
      "name": "AI agents COMPOSE a universe of interoperable apps over MCP (Holo Link, ADR-0060) — an agent builds capability κ-objects, composes them BY CONTENT ADDRESS (`extern … from \"κ\"`, including typed WIT-style `str` interfaces across isolated component memories), RUNS the composition (the linker resolves + verifies (L5) + links (L3) the dependency graph, no server) and SHARES it as one holo://κ; `holo_build` surfaces a composition's dependency κ's in `imports`. The composition is itself a κ — a first-class object that flows into Own (ADR-0053) · Settle (ADR-0048) · Orchestrate (ADR-0045), which operate on any κ. The universe of apps, agent-driven",
      "hosc:authority": "W3C Model Context Protocol (2024-11-05) · W3C WebAssembly Core 2.0 (imports/linking) · IETF RFC 8785 (JCS) · W3C PROV-O + DID Core · UOR-ADDR (κ = H(canonical_form)) · holospaces Laws L1/L3/L5",
      "hosc:witness": "tools/holo-compose-mcp-witness.mjs",
      "hosc:required": true,
      "hosc:category": "Compute & verifiable builds"
