      "name": "SOLANA SPOT LIQUIDITY, native in the one wallet seam (Holo Swap): Jupiter is the WDK Swidge provider for Solana spot — the Solana counterpart of the Hyperliquid perps write side, so one verifiable terminal reaches perps (Hyperliquid) AND spot (Solana) through the SAME default-deny wallet. Jupiter's route is computed OFF-CHAIN and is never trusted; it is enforced on-chain by re-derivation: the sealed venue descriptor (etc/holo-chains/jupiter.uor.json) re-derives to its κ so a swapped host/program is refused; an INDEPENDENTLY re-derived min-out floor refuses a threshold weaker than the chosen slippage; the BUILT transaction must invoke the sealed Jupiter program AND be paid by the wallet's own key (anti-phishing is structural); the swap is SIMULATED before signing; and the key signs only behind the human gate, which is shown the verified, simulation-passed numbers. The quote is input; the chain is the judge",
      "hosc:authority": "Jupiter (developers.jup.ag) consumed by reference (Law L4) · UOR-ADDR (κ = H(canonical_form)) · IETF RFC 8785 (JCS) · CAIP-2 (solana:) · holospaces Laws L1/L4/L5 · holo-solana (ed25519 κ) + holo-wdk (default-deny gate) by reference",
